staff and campus visitors, the University of North Texas (“UNT”) prohibits smoking anywhere on university property and limits the use of smokeless tobacco products and electronic cigarettes on the UNT campus. See full policy (PDF):  Smoke-Free Campus Attachments:  Smoke-Free Campus ProceduresPolicy owner: VP for Finance and AdministrationPolicy contact:  Elizabeth WithVP for Student AffairsDivision of Student Affairs940-565-4909Elizabeth.With@unt.edu Applies to: Faculty, Staff, Students, All UniversityDate Issued: Monday, November 19, 2012References: Tobacco-Free WorkplaceCross-References:  Tobacco-Free Workplace Last updated:  Date: 2012-11-19Action: New PolicyComments: UNT Policy "Smoke-Free Campus Policy" was created to protect the health and welfare of everyone on UNT's campus. Policy effective 1/1/2013. Top Main Menu Home FAQ Policy manual Resources Policy updates About the Policy Office University Links MyUNT Blackboard EagleConnect UNT Directory UNT Map UNT Calendar Jobs at UNT Give to UNT Email & Phone  policy@unt.edu  940-565-4535 University Policy Office   Find UNT on Google Maps   1155 Union Circle #311277 Denton, Texas 76203-5017   Visitor Information Call us Email Us UNT Map Apply now Schedule a tour Get more info Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy | Electronic Accessibility | Required Links | UNT Home ©2017 University of North Texas Required Links 